cs.NI, cs.MA, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper deals with wireless sensor networks and their communication protocols, which falls under the scope of cs.NI. 
2. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper discusses the use of transmit-only sensors and regular sensors (cluster-heads) to achieve performance goals, which can be seen as a multi-agent system. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the communication between transmit-only sensors and cluster-heads, which can be seen as a distributed computing problem. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes packet admission policies to achieve performance goals, which can be seen as a control problem. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses a mathematical model to evaluate packet admission policies, which can be seen as an information theory problem.
